<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880118-0124 </DOCNO><HL> LTV Gets Contract To Continue Output Of Army Rockets </HL><SO> </SO><CO> LTV GD RTN MD GM ITT HSC T </CO><IN> ARO </IN><G> DEF </G><TEXT>   LTV Corp. said it won a $242.5 million Army contract to continue production of the Multiple Launch Rocket System. The award, covering 72,000 rockets and related equipment, is part of a seven-year contract initiated in 1983.    General Dynamics Corp. got a $163.5 million Navy contract for Standard shipboard air-defense missiles, and Raytheon Co. won a $130.6 million contract for Standard missiles.    McDonnell Douglas Corp. received a $161.8 million Air Force contract for Delta II space-launch vehicles.    Units of General Motors Corp. were issued contracts totaling $105.6 million for advanced medium-range air-to-air missiles for the Air Force and vehicle-transmission and helicopter-missile equipment for the Army.    ITT Corp. won a $47.4 million Navy contract for electronic equipment.    Science Applications International Corp. got a $25 million Air Force contract for design services.    BMY Co., a unit of Harsco Corp., was awarded a $19.4 million Army contract for armored vehicles.    ATandamp;T Technologies, a unit of American Telephone andamp; Telegraph Co., received a $17.8 million Navy contract for oceanographic services. </TEXT></DOC>